#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.124"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.124:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.124:0.2"
msgid "13. Gilānavagga "
msgstr "13. Sick "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: gilānūpaṭṭhākasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.124:0.3"
msgid "124. Dutiyaupaṭṭhākasutta "
msgstr "124. A Carer (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.124:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko nālaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a carer with five qualities is not competent to care for a patient. "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.3"
msgid "Nappaṭibalo hoti bhesajjaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ; "
msgstr "They’re unable to prepare medicine. "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.4"
msgid "sappāyāsappāyaṃ na jānāti, asappāyaṃ upanāmeti, sappāyaṃ apanāmeti; "
msgstr "They don’t know what is suitable and unsuitable, so they supply what is unsuitable and remove what is suitable. "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.5"
msgid "āmisantaro gilānaṃ upaṭṭhāti, no mettacitto; "
msgstr "They care for the sick for the sake of material benefits, not out of love. "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.6"
msgid "jegucchī hoti uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā vantaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā nīharituṃ; "
msgstr "They’re disgusted to remove feces, urine, vomit, or spit. "

#. VAR: nappaṭibalo → na paṭibalo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: samādapetuṃ → samādāpetuṃ (?)
msgctxt "an5.124:1.7"
msgid "nappaṭibalo hoti gilānaṃ kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ. "
msgstr "They’re unable to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the patient with a Dhamma talk from time to time. "

msgctxt "an5.124:1.8"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko nālaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr "A carer with these five qualities is not competent to care for a patient. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.145, sc2
msgctxt "an5.124:2.1"
msgid "Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko alaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr "A carer with five qualities is competent to care for a patient. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.3"
msgid "Paṭibalo hoti bhesajjaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ; "
msgstr "They’re able to prepare medicine. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.4"
msgid "sappāyāsappāyaṃ jānāti, asappāyaṃ apanāmeti, sappāyaṃ upanāmeti; "
msgstr "They know what is suitable and unsuitable, so they remove what is unsuitable and supply what is suitable. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.5"
msgid "mettacitto gilānaṃ upaṭṭhāti, no āmisantaro; "
msgstr "They care for the sick out of love, not for the sake of material benefits. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.6"
msgid "ajegucchī hoti uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā vantaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā nīharituṃ; "
msgstr "They’re not disgusted to remove feces, urine, vomit, or spit. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.7"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti gilānaṃ kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ. "
msgstr "They’re able to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the patient with a Dhamma talk from time to time. "

msgctxt "an5.124:2.8"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko alaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātun”ti. "
msgstr "A carer with these five qualities is competent to care for a patient.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.124:2.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

